WEBVTT

00:00.583 --> 00:01.250
(CROWD CLAMORING)

00:01.917 --> 00:03.959
Emily Dodson you're under arrest
for the conspiracy kidnapping

00:04.041 --> 00:05.041
of Charlie Dodson.

00:06.166 --> 00:07.709
JUDGE:
How does your client plead?

00:09.333 --> 00:10.250
Guilty.

00:11.250 --> 00:12.500
E.B. JONATHAN:
She said not guilty!

00:12.583 --> 00:14.083
Not guilty, Your Honor!

00:15.417 --> 00:17.667
You didn't kill your baby.

00:17.750 --> 00:19.000
Bad men did that.

00:19.083 --> 00:20.000
(GUNSHOTS)

00:20.083 --> 00:21.750
You really think Emily
was a part of it?

00:21.834 --> 00:23.125
DETECTIVE HOLCOMB:
She laid with the man

00:23.208 --> 00:24.375
that murdered your son.

00:24.959 --> 00:25.834
What is it, Della?

00:25.917 --> 00:27.333
DELLA: It's from Mr. Baggerly.

00:27.583 --> 00:28.917
I think we got fired.

00:29.583 --> 00:31.917
Sometimes I think this is
no longer my world.

00:33.417 --> 00:34.834
PAUL DRAKE:
I've been looking for you.

00:34.917 --> 00:36.041
Down in the alley

00:36.125 --> 00:38.875
I found dried blood
and this.

00:38.959 --> 00:41.041
What was George's body
even doing over at county?

00:41.625 --> 00:44.667
Did she kidnap little Charlie,
or did something else happen?

00:44.959 --> 00:46.458
Who killed you, George?

00:47.458 --> 00:49.542
Are we gonna be expecting
another surprise?

00:50.000 --> 00:51.333
Do you hear the voices?

00:52.166 --> 00:54.458
You don't have to worry
about Charlie Dodson.

00:54.834 --> 00:56.500
I'm going to resurrect him.

00:58.125 --> 00:59.166
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

01:06.583 --> 01:10.333
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

01:16.917 --> 01:19.125
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

01:30.458 --> 01:31.917
MOTHER:
We wanted Sister to know

01:32.000 --> 01:33.333
how much she's in our thoughts.

01:33.417 --> 01:35.750
We've rented a pew for, gosh,
how many years now?

01:35.834 --> 01:37.417
Oh, since before
Gloria was born.

01:37.500 --> 01:38.667
-Row 14.
-BIRDY MCKEEGAN: Oh.

01:38.750 --> 01:41.834
There's 50 of us that chip in,
we're all big tithers.

01:41.917 --> 01:43.417
Sister's heart will be warmed.

01:43.500 --> 01:45.667
GLORIA: "Each one must give
as he has decided

01:45.750 --> 01:49.041
in his heart,
for God loves a cheerful giver."

01:49.125 --> 01:51.583
-Second Corinthians.
-Memorized the whole thing.

01:51.667 --> 01:52.750
Remarkable.

01:52.834 --> 01:54.709
BIRDY: Sister, some visitors
to brighten your day.

01:54.792 --> 01:56.583
Nice of you folks
to look in on me.

01:56.667 --> 01:59.834
We're lost without you, Sister,
and we miss you.

01:59.917 --> 02:02.041
Well, I'll be back on my feet
in no time.

02:02.583 --> 02:03.875
That's a promise.

02:05.417 --> 02:07.041
What have you got there,
sweetheart?

02:07.125 --> 02:08.709
Don't be shy.

02:08.792 --> 02:10.959
Do you like sweets, Sister?

02:11.041 --> 02:13.750
I would eat them for breakfast,
lunch, and dinner if I could.

02:14.542 --> 02:15.834
Me too.

02:15.917 --> 02:18.542
Maybe we split some? Right now?
What do you say?

02:20.542 --> 02:21.667
(GASPS)

02:22.709 --> 02:23.959
(SCREAMS)

02:24.041 --> 02:26.208
GLORIA: The fear of the Lord
is hatred of evil.

02:26.291 --> 02:28.750
-Pride and arrogance
and perverted speech!
-Oh, God!

02:28.834 --> 02:31.959
-ELDER SEIDEL:
Sister, come. Come.
-MOTHER: The Lord rebukes you.

02:32.041 --> 02:34.041
The God of Peace will crush you.

02:34.792 --> 02:36.458
(CAR HORN HONKS)

02:42.583 --> 02:44.125
Today of all days.

02:51.166 --> 02:52.458
Shit.

02:55.583 --> 02:57.333
(ELIAS BIRCHARD JONATHAN GRUNTS)

02:57.417 --> 03:01.166
And now, we're bringing people
back from the dead.

03:01.250 --> 03:04.667
Perhaps I should announce
my love of communism

03:04.750 --> 03:07.041
to finish the icing
on this lovely cake.

03:07.125 --> 03:09.083
At least you're not the one
on trial.

03:09.166 --> 03:12.083
I am 100 percent the one
on trial.

03:12.166 --> 03:14.333
That's what it means
to be a defense attorney

03:14.417 --> 03:15.417
in this town.

03:15.500 --> 03:17.458
-When did you leave Emily?
-6:00 this morning.

03:17.542 --> 03:18.709
She was too scared to sleep

03:18.792 --> 03:20.875
and certainly bruised enough
to press charges

03:20.959 --> 03:22.875
-on those bastards.
-What's my day?

03:22.959 --> 03:24.917
Writing time,
promotions on discovery,

03:25.000 --> 03:26.917
suppression of statements,
and 1:00 p.m. interview

03:27.000 --> 03:29.000
-with the Beverly Hills Post--
-First thing's first.

03:29.083 --> 03:31.208
Let's see Judge Wright
for bail reduction.

03:31.291 --> 03:34.125
Great, and we can follow that
by filing a formal complaint

03:34.208 --> 03:37.250
-with the police commissioner.
-Cops investigating cops?

03:37.333 --> 03:39.166
(LAUGHS)
That's a trip for biscuits.

03:39.250 --> 03:40.875
Well, then,
we can file a civil suit

03:40.959 --> 03:42.750
for excessive force,
police misconduct--

03:42.834 --> 03:46.083
Della, the actions
of the police are a golden arrow

03:46.166 --> 03:48.583
-in my quiver.
-They brutalized her, E.B.

03:48.667 --> 03:52.625
My goal, our goal, remains
securing Emily's release,

03:52.709 --> 03:53.750
pending trial.

03:53.834 --> 03:56.709
Now, there are several avenues
that I can pursue

03:56.792 --> 03:59.041
to achieve that end.
(GRUNTS)

03:59.125 --> 04:02.834
But police thuggery, we save
for a judge and jury.

04:04.750 --> 04:09.000
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

04:11.875 --> 04:14.125
E.B.: They smacked her
around like a ragdoll.

04:14.208 --> 04:17.041
MAYNARD BARNES: Mr. Jonathan's
secretary has an imagination.

04:17.125 --> 04:19.083
Bring Emily in, Your Honor.
See for yourself.

04:19.166 --> 04:20.417
It's jail.

04:20.500 --> 04:23.417
Maybe the girl got roughed up,
but it wasn't by my detectives.

04:23.500 --> 04:25.542
Detectives?
Those men are savages.

04:25.625 --> 04:27.000
JUDGE FRED WRIGHT:
If you want a bail change,

04:27.083 --> 04:29.083
you need to show me a change
in circumstances.

04:29.166 --> 04:31.041
E.B.: My client
is in imminent danger.

04:31.125 --> 04:33.667
They tried to beat a confession
out of her.

04:33.750 --> 04:35.417
-(BARNES LAUGHS)
-Because your case

04:35.500 --> 04:37.041
is a bar of hand soap

04:37.125 --> 04:39.375
shrinking into nothing
every hour.

04:39.458 --> 04:42.792
My case against Emily Dodson
is stronger today than it was

04:42.875 --> 04:44.500
-just a few days ago.
-Soap.

04:44.583 --> 04:47.291
BARNES: Matthew Dodson
is cooperating with us.

04:47.375 --> 04:49.375
-What?
-He's waving spousal privilege,

04:49.458 --> 04:52.083
and is prepared
to testify against her.

04:52.166 --> 04:54.417
That-- That's news to me.

04:54.500 --> 04:56.709
Well, Mr. Dodson contacted us
just this morning.

04:56.792 --> 04:58.792
You'll have his
cooperation agreement

04:58.875 --> 05:00.250
by this afternoon.

05:00.333 --> 05:03.125
I'm ordering the D.A.
to move Mrs. Dodson

05:03.208 --> 05:05.875
-to protective custody.
-Thank you, Your Honor.

05:05.959 --> 05:08.125
JUDGE WRIGHT:
Only E.B. and his people
are allowed near her

05:08.208 --> 05:09.291
and Maynard,

05:09.375 --> 05:11.291
if I hear your detectives
are trying any shenanigans

05:11.375 --> 05:14.166
with that girl, you're gonna
have a big problem with me.

05:16.125 --> 05:18.250
-Bail stays the same.
-E.B.: No.

05:18.333 --> 05:20.709
I'll make sure the baby killer
is comfortable.

05:20.792 --> 05:23.125
If you'll excuse me,
I have a case to prepare.

05:25.667 --> 05:26.709
(DOOR CLOSES)

05:26.792 --> 05:28.792
E.B.: Oliver, is it me?

05:28.875 --> 05:31.792
Or was there a time
when Fred here

05:31.875 --> 05:33.709
wouldn't stand
for this type of show

05:33.792 --> 05:35.417
from the district attorney?

05:36.583 --> 05:38.875
Young man's game, E.B.

05:38.959 --> 05:41.500
Even the great Mr. Holmes
is retiring next week.

05:41.583 --> 05:42.875
He's 90.

05:42.959 --> 05:45.250
I've got 16 years on him.

05:46.750 --> 05:49.125
♪ (MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

05:49.208 --> 05:51.000
VIRGIL SHEETS:
This was you guys?

05:51.083 --> 05:53.875
-Sure was.
-VIRGIL: Wow.

05:53.959 --> 05:55.625
Should I show him
Chubby's shoe?

05:55.709 --> 05:57.709
-VIRGIL: His shoe?
-Show him the shoe.

05:59.291 --> 06:01.083
Wow, that is some shoe.

06:01.166 --> 06:04.709
-Hit me right in the noggin.
Have another pull there, Virg.
-(CHUCKLES)

06:05.750 --> 06:06.959
Here you go.

06:08.667 --> 06:11.083
Oh, you guys have all
the good stories.

06:11.166 --> 06:14.166
When I tell stories about work,
folks wanna run out of the room.

06:14.250 --> 06:15.875
Not us, we love your stories.

06:15.959 --> 06:17.542
Private detective,

06:17.625 --> 06:20.000
-that's-- that's adventure...
-(PLANE RUMBLES BY)

06:20.083 --> 06:22.709
...danger, excitement.

06:22.792 --> 06:25.125
PERRY MASON:
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

06:25.208 --> 06:26.500
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

06:26.583 --> 06:28.000
MASON: What'd I say?

06:28.083 --> 06:29.417
You don't wanna know.

06:29.500 --> 06:30.792
Muchas gracias.

06:31.291 --> 06:32.959
Secret password.

06:34.125 --> 06:35.375
Wow.

06:35.458 --> 06:37.417
Watch out for planes.

06:37.500 --> 06:40.959
♪ (UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

06:46.500 --> 06:48.208
-MASON: (LAUGHS) Welcome.
-(LAUGHS) There are--

06:48.291 --> 06:49.750
There are planes out there.

06:49.834 --> 06:51.291
I thought you lived
on a farm.

06:51.375 --> 06:53.417
-It is a farm.
-PETE STRICKLAND: Hey, sit down.

06:53.500 --> 06:55.709
-Where are the chickens?
-Chickens is a good idea.

06:55.792 --> 06:58.250
You get eggs, you get meat.
Sit.

06:58.333 --> 07:01.625
So, Virg, there's something
I wanna show ya.

07:01.709 --> 07:04.709
Is it, um, pornography?

07:05.500 --> 07:06.458
No.

07:06.542 --> 07:07.875
VIRGIL: It's just that...

07:07.959 --> 07:09.834
you guys tell all these stories
about...

07:09.917 --> 07:14.041
clandestine meetings
and tailing dames and...

07:14.583 --> 07:16.583
cheating wives.

07:16.667 --> 07:21.083
Well, I-- I could go get some
if you want, Virg.

07:21.166 --> 07:24.750
Pale formaldehyde.
dead, putrid bodies

07:24.834 --> 07:27.166
and the monotony of existence

07:28.208 --> 07:31.000
does a number
on a man's virility.

07:32.250 --> 07:34.583
You know, I can relate
to Mr. Carmichael.

07:34.667 --> 07:36.875
You know, for him, it's food.

07:36.959 --> 07:38.917
For others, it could be...

07:39.000 --> 07:42.125
imagining you're
just a few inches tall,

07:42.208 --> 07:45.542
and the woman hides you
away in her purse.

07:49.792 --> 07:53.208
Why don't I show you that thing
I was gonna show you?

07:54.834 --> 07:56.542
Ta da!

07:57.875 --> 07:59.375
That's a dead body.

07:59.458 --> 08:01.458
I told you he was an expert.

08:01.542 --> 08:04.291
-Holy cow, that's--
-MASON: Meet George Gannon.

08:04.375 --> 08:06.583
But you-- you stole a body.

08:06.667 --> 08:08.291
Hmm, just this one.

08:08.375 --> 08:09.709
Look, I can't be here.

08:10.542 --> 08:13.709
Virg, Virg. Virgil! Virgil!

08:15.208 --> 08:17.208
George Gannon didn't ice
those stiffs on Central Ave,

08:17.291 --> 08:19.166
and he didn't run home
and blow his own head off.

08:19.250 --> 08:20.375
Nope.

08:20.458 --> 08:22.834
-Well, how do you know?
-Show him.

08:22.917 --> 08:24.208
Because of this.

08:26.083 --> 08:28.375
(TEETH SQUELCH)

08:29.917 --> 08:32.834
This denture was found
in an alleyway

08:32.917 --> 08:34.959
behind that apartment building.

08:35.041 --> 08:37.500
It fits perfectly
in Mr. Gannon's mouth here.

08:37.583 --> 08:40.166
And I'm no expert like you are,
but that's a bullet hole

08:40.250 --> 08:41.959
in his shoulder
and a hip that don't look right.

08:42.041 --> 08:44.917
We think George was murdered
that night with the others.

08:45.000 --> 08:47.625
You guys are breaking
so many laws right now.

08:47.709 --> 08:50.625
That's-- That's how you get
all the good stories, Virg.

08:50.709 --> 08:53.375
MASON: We need you to give
George here a proper autopsy

08:53.458 --> 08:54.792
because the police report
is a fairytale,

08:54.875 --> 08:56.041
and you're gonna help me
prove that.

08:56.125 --> 08:58.417
But you stole his body
from the county coroner.

08:58.500 --> 09:00.208
I can't just write
another autopsy

09:00.291 --> 09:02.250
in your-- your-- your pioneer
root cellar.

09:02.333 --> 09:03.959
And Jesus Christ,
you stole a body

09:04.041 --> 09:06.375
from Frank A. Nance.
I mean, who does that?

09:06.458 --> 09:07.625
MASON:
Frank Nance fucked up.

09:07.709 --> 09:10.166
He fucked up, Virg. He was--
He was told to fuck up.

09:10.250 --> 09:13.458
Now, I need you--
I need you to be the hero

09:13.542 --> 09:15.709
-that makes this right.
-No, I don't wanna be a hero.

09:15.792 --> 09:17.959
-MASON: Yes, you do!
-Oh, God, Mason, please.

09:18.041 --> 09:19.458
Don't do this to me.

09:19.542 --> 09:21.417
You guys said
we were gonna have fun.

09:21.500 --> 09:23.083
Well... (SCOFFS)

09:23.166 --> 09:26.125
-Ain't we having fun, Virg?
-Right?

09:28.125 --> 09:29.959
PETE: Let's go upstairs.

09:30.041 --> 09:31.333
We'll get a bottle.

09:31.417 --> 09:33.959
And you can tell us
more about you

09:34.041 --> 09:35.750
being in a lady's purse.

09:35.834 --> 09:39.166
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

09:42.000 --> 09:43.583
(VIRGIL GROANS)

09:43.667 --> 09:47.834
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

09:59.667 --> 10:03.583
When we study law,
we are studying not a mystery,

10:03.667 --> 10:04.917
but a profession.

10:05.000 --> 10:07.542
The reason why
it is a profession,

10:07.625 --> 10:09.417
it is, uh...

10:09.500 --> 10:11.583
Della, did you get a hold
of National City?

10:11.667 --> 10:12.750
4:00 p.m.

10:12.834 --> 10:14.667
And it is Howard Brown?

10:14.750 --> 10:18.625
Uh, a Mr. Tod Robbins.
Howard Brown wasn't available.

10:18.709 --> 10:20.875
-Who the hell is Tod Robbins?
-REPORTER: (CLEARS THROAT) Um.

10:20.959 --> 10:24.250
"The reason it is a profession,"
Oliver Wendell Holmes?

10:27.041 --> 10:30.166
I came to this little pueblo
about a year

10:30.250 --> 10:32.792
before he ascended
to the Supreme Court.

10:32.875 --> 10:34.166
-REPORTER: Oh.
-Since that time,

10:34.250 --> 10:37.375
Justice Holmes has distinguished
himself as...

10:37.458 --> 10:40.375
the nation's foremost jurist

10:40.458 --> 10:43.458
and Los Angeles
has disgraced itself

10:43.542 --> 10:45.625
as a Gomorrah
where truth is bought

10:45.709 --> 10:50.709
and sold like the head
of a-- of a... rutabaga.

10:50.792 --> 10:52.458
What are you waving about?

10:52.542 --> 10:55.792
He just wants me
out of the picture, Chief.

10:55.875 --> 10:59.709
This is why I have taken up
the cause of Emily Dodson.

10:59.792 --> 11:03.500
When a state aims
its annihilating power

11:03.583 --> 11:07.959
against a mere individual,
who will stand up against it?

11:08.041 --> 11:09.917
Who will defend the defenseless?

11:10.000 --> 11:14.750
Who will fight for justice
against a heartless expediency?

11:14.834 --> 11:19.125
This is what your readers
need to know.

11:19.208 --> 11:21.333
-(CAMERA FLASHBULB POPS)
-REPORTER: Yes, of course. Uh...

11:21.417 --> 11:23.959
Something else our readers
would like to know.

11:24.041 --> 11:27.250
Where do you go to eat
when you have a night out?

11:31.250 --> 11:35.083
I am fond of the French dip
at Phillipe's.

11:35.166 --> 11:37.166
DOCTOR BUNDY:
From a medical perspective,

11:37.250 --> 11:40.375
what occurred on stage
was an epileptic seizure.

11:40.458 --> 11:43.166
The sister has a history
of these episodes.

11:43.250 --> 11:46.333
And they can be treated
with a program of bromides

11:46.417 --> 11:47.542
or Luminal.

11:47.625 --> 11:51.709
But they won't do much good
without rest and relaxation.

11:51.792 --> 11:54.709
Otherwise, you're asking
for a recurrence.

11:54.792 --> 11:57.125
How long before
she can return to work?

11:57.208 --> 11:59.208
-DOCTOR BUNDY: Several weeks.
-Oh.

11:59.291 --> 12:02.041
I cannot allow her to resume
the schedule she was on.

12:02.125 --> 12:04.041
Dr. Bundy, you do not have
that authority.

12:04.125 --> 12:05.375
We-- We appreciate
your observation--

12:05.458 --> 12:06.792
Her schedule
is what brought about--

12:06.875 --> 12:08.417
Sister has had
these episodes before,

12:08.500 --> 12:10.166
and she's risen stronger
each time.

12:10.250 --> 12:12.041
In the meantime, we need
to tighten security

12:12.125 --> 12:13.333
around the mansion.

12:13.417 --> 12:16.792
And I will lead the temple
in worship.

12:21.709 --> 12:25.041
ELDER BROWN:
No offense, Birdy, but...

12:25.125 --> 12:28.375
you're not the orator
your daughter is...

12:28.458 --> 12:30.917
nor are you the one
to walk back the heresy

12:31.000 --> 12:32.417
that went out on the wire.

12:32.500 --> 12:33.625
(LAUGHS) Heresy?

12:33.709 --> 12:36.125
ELDER BROWN: We're not running
a tent revival anymore.

12:36.208 --> 12:40.000
We've scaled back the speaking
in tongues and miracle healings.

12:40.083 --> 12:43.709
Let's leave raising the dead
to Christ our Father.

12:43.792 --> 12:46.625
ELDER SEIDEL: The ramifications
of this latest message,

12:46.709 --> 12:50.834
the Sister's unavailability,
threatens the financial health

12:50.917 --> 12:54.667
of the assembly
and every elder in this room.

12:54.750 --> 12:56.250
Wouldn't you agree, Herman?

12:56.333 --> 12:58.083
HERMAN BAGGERLY:
No one has lost more than me.

12:58.166 --> 13:00.375
A hundred thousand dollars
burned in a chimney

13:00.458 --> 13:02.208
by conspirators...

13:02.291 --> 13:06.250
one of which our church
publicly supports.

13:06.333 --> 13:08.625
Brother Herman, it has not
escaped my notice

13:08.709 --> 13:12.000
that you vacated your seat
on stage for the pews.

13:12.083 --> 13:13.959
It's a wonder
I'm still in the building.

13:14.041 --> 13:16.291
BIRDY: I know it's--
it's been a challenging time.

13:16.375 --> 13:18.750
-But a faith untested is a--
-HERMAN: You do not know.

13:18.834 --> 13:22.208
Offense is taken every time
the Sister speaks

13:22.291 --> 13:24.208
for my Matthew's harlot wife.

13:25.166 --> 13:27.166
I won't go on playing the rube.

13:28.291 --> 13:32.291
This church can no longer afford
to teeter on the whims

13:32.375 --> 13:33.542
of hysterical women.

13:33.625 --> 13:35.291
ELDER BROWN:
We need to prepare a statement

13:35.375 --> 13:38.250
renouncing what the Sister
promised under her seizure.

13:38.333 --> 13:41.291
Sister receives messages
from God.

13:41.375 --> 13:44.291
Those messages are the bedrock
of our church.

13:44.375 --> 13:47.041
Absurdity! The cruelty...

13:47.125 --> 13:49.333
of suggesting that she could
bring the child

13:49.417 --> 13:50.625
back from the dead.

13:50.709 --> 13:53.458
You cannot pick and choose
which messages to believe

13:53.542 --> 13:55.083
based on your convenience.

13:58.750 --> 14:00.750
We decided this as a group.

14:04.750 --> 14:07.000
Away from hysterical women.

14:07.083 --> 14:08.959
ELDER BROWN:
You will censor the Sister,

14:09.041 --> 14:12.083
or the spigot will be
turned off.

14:12.166 --> 14:14.625
ELDER SEIDEL: I'm afraid
it's not a discussion,
Mother McKeegan.

14:17.542 --> 14:19.583
Elder Brown will lead worship.

14:20.500 --> 14:23.542
I'll advise Sister
of your recommendations

14:24.417 --> 14:27.667
when she's regained
her strength.

14:27.750 --> 14:31.834
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

14:37.875 --> 14:39.000
(ELEVATOR DINGS)

14:44.083 --> 14:45.750
TOD ROBBINS:
I've reviewed your situation,

14:45.834 --> 14:48.917
taking into consideration
the entirety of your--

14:49.000 --> 14:50.000
your holdings.

14:50.083 --> 14:52.208
That's your savings,
stocks, and bonds.

14:52.291 --> 14:55.041
Didn't fare too poorly
in the crash, considering.

14:55.125 --> 14:56.542
TOD: No, sir. Not at all.

14:56.625 --> 14:58.000
We also looked at your income,

14:58.083 --> 15:00.417
income sources,
potential collateral.

15:00.500 --> 15:01.917
E.B.: Meaning my house?

15:02.000 --> 15:03.875
Three mortgages on it, yes.

15:03.959 --> 15:06.333
Your car, all of that.

15:06.417 --> 15:10.542
It is my unfortunate duty
to inform you that...

15:10.625 --> 15:15.208
twenty-five thousand is simply
not a number we would be...

15:15.291 --> 15:16.542
comfortable with.

15:16.625 --> 15:17.583
I'm sorry?

15:17.667 --> 15:20.250
You see, the numbers here
do not add up

15:20.333 --> 15:21.792
-nearly close enough--
-I asked...

15:21.875 --> 15:23.083
to meet with Howard Brown.

15:23.166 --> 15:26.500
TOD: As I mentioned,
Howard is no longer with us.

15:26.583 --> 15:29.083
He and his wife
moved to Carpinteria,

15:29.166 --> 15:31.166
-for the air, I think.
-Son,

15:31.250 --> 15:33.750
I've got a lot of years
with this bank.

15:33.834 --> 15:35.000
Put in a call to Howard.

15:35.083 --> 15:38.041
I spoke with
the branch manager, sir.

15:38.125 --> 15:39.834
And he also regrets
to inform you--

15:39.917 --> 15:41.417
Are you saying
I'm not good for it?

15:41.500 --> 15:45.417
That my loyalty, that my word,
and my relationship

15:45.500 --> 15:48.792
with this institution,
with Howard--

15:48.875 --> 15:51.667
I'm only asking
for a goddamn measly loan.

15:51.750 --> 15:53.125
A four-month loan.

15:53.208 --> 15:55.458
TOD: I understand that,
Mr. Jonathan.

15:55.542 --> 15:56.625
I've got my savings.

15:56.709 --> 15:58.291
TOD: Your savings
are propping up your law office,

15:58.375 --> 15:59.542
and your mortgages--

16:01.333 --> 16:04.417
♪ (SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

16:07.250 --> 16:09.625
DELLA STREET:
Why didn't you tell me
the office was under water?

16:09.709 --> 16:10.917
E.B.: Mind your damn business.

16:12.875 --> 16:15.500
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

16:15.583 --> 16:17.625
RADIO ANNOUNCER:
...Warner Brothers Studios.

16:17.709 --> 16:21.041
And now, to draw to a close,
a very stirring number

16:21.125 --> 16:22.333
with a dazzling...

16:22.417 --> 16:25.542
OLIVER FOGG: Have you considered
where your eternal remains

16:25.625 --> 16:27.583
will be laid to rest,
Miss. Prystock?

16:27.667 --> 16:30.583
Not terribly much, Mr. Fogg.

16:30.667 --> 16:32.041
Then allow me to extoll

16:32.125 --> 16:34.667
the sylvan virtues
of Forest Lawn,

16:34.750 --> 16:37.709
set amidst the undisturbed
nature of Glendale.

16:37.792 --> 16:39.750
Sylvan virtues, he says.

16:39.834 --> 16:42.625
OLIVER: Three hundred acres,
forever tranquil,

16:42.709 --> 16:44.667
with very reasonable
monthly payments

16:44.750 --> 16:47.792
and headstones carved
in red Italian marble.

16:47.875 --> 16:50.583
Hmm, someone looks ready
for burial right now.

16:50.667 --> 16:52.250
Long day.

16:52.333 --> 16:55.458
Locking lips
with Chubby Carmichael, were ya?

16:55.542 --> 16:56.875
DELLA: No, goodness.

16:56.959 --> 17:00.291
He's a married man, Della.
You should know better.

17:01.709 --> 17:05.000
What's a dead man want
with red marble, Mr. Fogg?

17:05.083 --> 17:07.834
To memorialize
a life well lived, of course.

17:07.917 --> 17:10.709
-DELLA: Is this--
-OLIVER:
Cod, from the genus Gadus,

17:10.792 --> 17:13.458
creamed beyond recognition.

17:13.542 --> 17:16.208
When you check yourself
into the Biltmore,

17:16.291 --> 17:18.709
you can make
your food requests known.

17:18.792 --> 17:21.792
He didn't mean anything
by it, June. See?

17:21.875 --> 17:24.959
♪ (LOUNGE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

17:27.083 --> 17:28.959
You get your Mrs. Emily out?

17:30.792 --> 17:32.500
Take a load off, Dell.

17:32.583 --> 17:34.750
I'm gonna take it upstairs...

17:34.834 --> 17:37.000
pretend I'm still a kid
back home

17:37.083 --> 17:39.500
and anything is possible.

17:46.709 --> 17:48.959
(GOLFER 1 GROANS)

17:49.041 --> 17:51.250
-It's the Santa Ana.
-There's no Santa Ana.

17:51.333 --> 17:54.750
-You feel it, don't you?
-GOLFER 2:
Leave the kid out of it.

17:54.834 --> 17:56.750
Go spot the ball, huh?

17:56.834 --> 17:59.458
(METAL CLANKING)

18:00.834 --> 18:02.875
Five bucks says I could bean him
from here.

18:02.959 --> 18:06.083
-(IMITATING CHUBBY CARMICHAEL)
Hey, cut it out now.
-Oh, man, that guy.

18:06.166 --> 18:07.500
See those pictures in the paper?

18:07.583 --> 18:09.959
Uh, is it me or does printing
a black bar

18:10.041 --> 18:12.792
over your jimmy
make it look worse?

18:12.875 --> 18:14.166
GOLFER 2:
What the hell's up now?

18:14.250 --> 18:16.834
GOLFER 1: Hey, kid,
those are Tommy Armour specials.

18:17.166 --> 18:18.291
Kid!

18:19.333 --> 18:22.500
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

18:24.709 --> 18:26.875
-Oh!
-Oh, God.

18:30.542 --> 18:34.208
(GURNEY CLANKS)

18:39.583 --> 18:42.542
Oh, smells like
someone had quite a night.

18:42.625 --> 18:44.750
Unless you're working on
Old Overholt himself.

18:44.834 --> 18:46.959
I wish I could pull
my own brain out.

18:47.041 --> 18:48.041
It's killing me.

18:48.125 --> 18:50.083
Oh, I'd offer you
an eye-opener, but they...

18:50.166 --> 18:51.542
tell me drink's illegal.

18:53.959 --> 18:55.041
God love you.

18:55.125 --> 18:56.375
Someone has to.

19:00.959 --> 19:02.375
What do we got here?

19:02.959 --> 19:04.083
John Doe,

19:04.166 --> 19:06.667
found him in a sand trap
with his head blown off.

19:07.834 --> 19:08.875
Naked.

19:09.875 --> 19:13.208
(METAL CLANKING)

19:16.709 --> 19:18.041
Those fuckers!

19:19.208 --> 19:20.834
-E.B.: Golf course?
-MASON: We had to make sure

19:20.917 --> 19:22.750
it was the right place so that
he would end up

19:22.834 --> 19:24.208
on Virgil's slab.

19:24.291 --> 19:26.750
So, what it means, E.B.,
is that you now get

19:26.834 --> 19:29.375
a second official autopsy
on the same body,

19:29.458 --> 19:31.542
but this one
will have a shattered left hip,

19:31.625 --> 19:33.083
and a bullet wound
in the shoulder.

19:33.166 --> 19:34.500
And that means what, again?

19:34.583 --> 19:36.667
You try shifting gears
in New Year's traffic

19:36.750 --> 19:38.417
with a bum arm and no left hip.

19:38.500 --> 19:41.083
Oh, I got a client who wants
to tell the whole world

19:41.166 --> 19:42.208
she's guilty.

19:42.291 --> 19:45.000
I went from Herman Baggerly
to working pro bono.

19:45.083 --> 19:46.083
And now this.

19:46.166 --> 19:48.041
This is a huge, huge break.

19:48.125 --> 19:50.542
Drake gave us the dentures,
he told us the blood trail

19:50.625 --> 19:52.750
went up the fire escape,
not down.

19:52.834 --> 19:54.125
PETE:
We figured George got plugged

19:54.208 --> 19:56.667
with the two Polacks,
tried to escape via the hallway,

19:56.750 --> 19:58.458
-via the roof...
-And got the heave-ho

19:58.542 --> 20:00.208
off the building
by the actual killer.

20:00.291 --> 20:01.583
You're saying
there's a fourth man?

20:01.667 --> 20:03.542
There was a fourth man
in the room.

20:03.625 --> 20:05.041
It was the two Polacks,
George...

20:05.125 --> 20:06.834
-E.B. : And who?
-I don't know that yet.

20:06.917 --> 20:09.458
And this Drake,
he's gonna testify to all this?

20:09.542 --> 20:11.041
MASON: Not a chance.
Police already made

20:11.125 --> 20:12.291
their evidence fit the story.

20:12.375 --> 20:13.583
Which pins it all on Gannon.

20:13.667 --> 20:16.208
But we know he was
already dead in the alleyway.

20:16.291 --> 20:18.000
How am I gonna get this
into evidence?

20:18.083 --> 20:20.542
That's what you're so good at.
And it's the truth.

20:20.625 --> 20:22.709
The truth won't move
wind chimes.

20:22.792 --> 20:24.000
I need more than this.

20:24.083 --> 20:25.500
We'll get you more.

20:26.959 --> 20:29.875
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

20:29.959 --> 20:31.041
E.B.: All right.

20:31.125 --> 20:33.750
With the caveat that we never
had this conversation,

20:33.834 --> 20:36.667
tell it to me one more time.
Load my lips.

20:36.750 --> 20:40.375
George Gannon
did not kill himself.

20:40.458 --> 20:42.417
There was a fourth man.

20:42.500 --> 20:45.709
There's a fourth man.
A baby-killer on the loose.

20:45.792 --> 20:46.875
How's that for a headline?

20:46.959 --> 20:49.542
Of course,
I'm not going in that direction,

20:49.625 --> 20:54.709
but I did think that I owe you
a taste of what we've dug up.

20:54.792 --> 20:58.542
Just so that you have a chance
to save some face.

20:58.625 --> 20:59.709
Professional courtesy.

20:59.792 --> 21:01.583
Always the gentleman, E.B.

21:01.667 --> 21:04.792
George Gannon
did not commit suicide.

21:04.875 --> 21:07.583
The suicide note
was donkey dust.

21:07.667 --> 21:08.917
The crime scene was staged.

21:09.000 --> 21:11.250
-By this fourth man.
-E.B.: Fourth man.

21:11.333 --> 21:14.333
That's right.
Not sure of his identity yet.

21:14.417 --> 21:17.458
But with the information
I have right here

21:17.542 --> 21:20.333
and the investigative powers
of your office,

21:20.417 --> 21:23.208
we'll get to the bottom
of this mess forthwith.

21:23.291 --> 21:26.792
(CHUCKLES) And in return
for this courtesy?

21:26.875 --> 21:29.834
Drop the charges
against my client.

21:29.917 --> 21:33.000
(LAUGHS)

21:34.166 --> 21:35.458
What do you got in there?

21:35.542 --> 21:38.125
Drop the charges,
I'll lift the latch.

21:38.208 --> 21:41.125
Short of that, the particulars
need to stay with me.

21:41.208 --> 21:45.041
I have a legal duty
to my client, Emily Dodson.

21:46.375 --> 21:48.709
Are you enjoying this, E.B.?

21:49.583 --> 21:52.208
I am, Mr. District Attorney.

21:52.291 --> 21:54.125
BARNES:
Let's relish it then, huh?

21:54.208 --> 21:58.625
Let's remember
this feeling of victory, huh?

21:58.709 --> 22:00.333
-(DRAWER OPENS)
-Now, what are--

22:00.417 --> 22:04.125
what are your legal duties
to Quentin Bates?

22:04.208 --> 22:06.125
-Quentin Bates?
-BARNES: Or Birch Corp,

22:06.208 --> 22:08.375
or Walter Thompson.

22:08.458 --> 22:10.500
Let's see.
Foster's Tool and Dye.

22:10.583 --> 22:11.500
Who?

22:11.583 --> 22:14.959
What about your legal duties
to Stella Chrome?

22:15.041 --> 22:17.250
You know former clients
of mine, congratulations.

22:17.333 --> 22:20.291
You stole from those clients
to keep from going under.

22:20.375 --> 22:21.542
That's an outright lie.

22:21.625 --> 22:23.834
You sure you wanna stand
by that? It's all right here,

22:23.917 --> 22:26.041
with the particulars,
as you put it.

22:26.125 --> 22:28.500
I never stole from my clients.
I paid back every penny.

22:28.583 --> 22:31.250
Misappropriated client
escrow funds,

22:31.333 --> 22:33.291
that's grand larceny
under the law.

22:33.375 --> 22:36.125
We all hit hard times
before the war.

22:36.208 --> 22:38.333
Everyone's moved
a little something.

22:38.417 --> 22:39.834
Oh, come on.

22:39.917 --> 22:42.500
Let's hope the bar association
footnotes that fact

22:42.583 --> 22:45.834
in your disbarment order.

22:45.917 --> 22:48.667
There's no way you'd be
dredging up old ghosts

22:48.750 --> 22:52.333
if you had a solid case.
No way. My boy Mason's right.

22:52.417 --> 22:53.583
BARNES:
You got three options here.

22:53.667 --> 22:56.458
Plead Emily Dodson out,
take the case to trail,

22:56.542 --> 22:59.709
or get yourself disbarred,

22:59.792 --> 23:04.083
and that's the kind of news
that makes the cover

23:04.166 --> 23:06.583
of the Law Journal, kid.

23:06.667 --> 23:08.000
She's innocent.

23:08.083 --> 23:09.709
BARNES:
This goes out on Friday noon.

23:09.792 --> 23:10.959
You let me know.

23:12.166 --> 23:13.625
There's the door.

23:16.083 --> 23:18.250
CHOIR: (SINGING)
♪ Every time I ♪

23:18.333 --> 23:20.625
♪ Feel this feeling ♪

23:20.709 --> 23:22.834
♪ Moving in my heart... ♪

23:24.000 --> 23:25.542
-That's enough.
-No.

23:25.625 --> 23:27.041
You're not on the pulpit now,

23:27.125 --> 23:29.083
it's enough when I say
it's enough.

23:29.166 --> 23:31.834
-Oh, come on. Don't be a brat.
-You don't listen.

23:31.917 --> 23:34.083
BIRDY: No, that's your problem,
daughter.

23:34.166 --> 23:36.000
-Sister.
-Daughter.

23:36.083 --> 23:38.542
We had an agreement
about Emily Dodson.

23:38.625 --> 23:41.250
-God thought otherwise.
-Oh, stop with that.

23:41.333 --> 23:43.583
I sent everyone downstairs,
it's just us.

23:43.667 --> 23:45.417
SISTER ALICE MCKEEGAN:
Do you hear that singing?

23:45.500 --> 23:48.250
Yes, it's your audience,

23:48.333 --> 23:49.917
come to keep vigil.

23:50.000 --> 23:52.208
Half of them wanna kiss
your feet.

23:52.291 --> 23:53.750
The other half wanna kill you.

23:53.834 --> 23:55.417
We've got bodyguards
in the living room.

23:55.500 --> 23:59.500
Reporters climbing in windows.
Elder Brown licking his chops.

23:59.583 --> 24:01.709
(SIGHS)
How am I to make this right?

24:01.792 --> 24:03.125
That's not your job.

24:03.208 --> 24:05.125
That's all my job is...

24:05.208 --> 24:06.959
letting you run wild
on our stage.

24:07.041 --> 24:09.583
And I run myself sick
chasing your revelations.

24:09.667 --> 24:11.792
What was true in the Bible
will be true again.

24:11.875 --> 24:14.291
BIRDY: Oh, come on.
I came up with that.

24:14.375 --> 24:17.291
You-- You had an episode.
You misspoke.

24:17.375 --> 24:18.750
I did not.

24:19.709 --> 24:21.375
It was real, Mama.

24:21.458 --> 24:22.875
You misheard.

24:23.709 --> 24:25.750
Did I mishear him in Oklahoma?

24:27.792 --> 24:30.083
He speaks, we do. You said that.

24:30.166 --> 24:32.333
You think I want this, Mama?

24:32.417 --> 24:34.333
Do you think I want God
in my head?

24:34.417 --> 24:37.000
You have a gift.
You have a spirit

24:37.083 --> 24:38.875
that moves people,

24:38.959 --> 24:41.417
changes people, saves people.

24:41.500 --> 24:44.125
Don't let your vanity
squander it.

24:44.208 --> 24:47.542
And if you truly believe God
told you to do this,

24:47.625 --> 24:49.709
then you get his attention back.

24:50.709 --> 24:53.166
And you tell him
it can't be done.

24:53.250 --> 24:55.333
-But it was--
-No, because it can't.

24:55.417 --> 24:57.834
A box full of snakes
from our own people.

24:57.917 --> 24:59.083
You-- You--

25:01.333 --> 25:03.542
You have to let me protect you.

25:03.625 --> 25:05.542
You have to let me be
your mother.

25:06.417 --> 25:07.542
Hmm?

25:07.625 --> 25:12.291
♪ (CHOIR CONTINUES SINGING) ♪

25:15.834 --> 25:17.625
-BARNES: He's a what?
-Civil rights attorney.

25:17.709 --> 25:20.208
He's suing the police department
for joining a vigilante mob

25:20.291 --> 25:21.625
that dragged him out
out of his hotel.

25:21.709 --> 25:23.208
Write it up and bother me later.

25:32.583 --> 25:33.917
-Frank.
-Hey, Maynard.

25:34.000 --> 25:36.333
-Get the fuck out.
-I'm peeing.

25:36.417 --> 25:37.875
Pinch it off,
stand outside,

25:37.959 --> 25:40.709
make sure no one comes in.
Now.

25:40.792 --> 25:43.458
(THUDDING)

25:47.291 --> 25:48.917
-Frank.
-FRANK: Yeah.

25:49.000 --> 25:50.792
BARNES:
Did you wash your hands?

25:55.291 --> 25:57.959
(WATER TRICKLES)

26:03.000 --> 26:03.917
(DOOR CLOSES)

26:04.000 --> 26:06.750
What level of fuck-up
am I looking at on

26:06.834 --> 26:08.208
People V. Dodson?

26:08.291 --> 26:10.000
Detective Holcomb, is it some...

26:10.083 --> 26:12.917
standard ground-floor form?

26:13.000 --> 26:14.583
You and--
you and junior here

26:14.667 --> 26:16.875
give a little help
with the crime scene?

26:16.959 --> 26:18.583
With all respect, sir,
I got no idea

26:18.667 --> 26:21.375
-what you're talking about.
-Who killed Charlie Dodson?

26:22.333 --> 26:26.333
HOLCOMB: (SIGHS)
Uh, hard to say. Uh...

26:26.417 --> 26:30.291
George Gannon,
one of the other two mugs.

26:30.375 --> 26:32.709
If you want us to get specific,
we can do that.

26:32.792 --> 26:34.542
Yeah.
I want you to be specific

26:34.625 --> 26:36.917
'cause I got
Oliver Wendell Jonathan

26:37.000 --> 26:39.792
blowing some fourth man smoke
in my face.

26:39.875 --> 26:40.917
Why would he do that?

26:41.000 --> 26:42.583
'Cause he's desperate
and got no case.

26:42.667 --> 26:45.083
DETECTIVE HOLCOMB:
If we'd had another 30 minutes,
you'd have a confession.

26:45.166 --> 26:48.583
(SCOFFS) Thirty minutes? You had
three fucking days, detective!

26:48.667 --> 26:50.625
Couldn't break
a fucking housewife!

26:51.875 --> 26:53.834
You arrested
the wrong fucking guy.

26:55.333 --> 26:57.750
DETECTIVE ENNIS:
It was your office, sir,

26:57.834 --> 26:59.959
that pushed us to arrest
Mathew Dodson.

27:00.041 --> 27:01.625
That's on you.

27:01.709 --> 27:04.750
Detective Holcomb here
has done some ace work.

27:04.834 --> 27:07.083
Dodson's lawyer ain't got shit.

27:08.291 --> 27:11.083
Says his guy knows different.

27:11.166 --> 27:14.917
-Who, Perry Mason? He's a bum.
-BARNES: Mm-hmm. Yeah.

27:15.000 --> 27:17.125
Only a bum would hire him.

27:17.208 --> 27:19.208
There's no fourth man,

27:19.291 --> 27:20.959
and the housewife,
she knew plenty.

27:21.041 --> 27:22.250
It's tight, sir.

27:22.333 --> 27:24.458
Yeah. It ain't that tight,

27:24.542 --> 27:27.041
and it sure as fuck
ain't "ace work."

27:27.875 --> 27:29.834
You better pray E.B.'s bum

27:29.917 --> 27:31.750
ain't playing this better
than you are.

27:31.834 --> 27:35.375
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

27:38.500 --> 27:40.417
MASON: Linda, you're--
you're right. You're ab--

27:40.500 --> 27:42.166
You're absolutely in the right,
again.

27:42.250 --> 27:43.291
I-- I-- I shouldn't--

27:43.375 --> 27:46.208
I shouldn't have yelled.
But if you had just paid

27:46.291 --> 27:47.500
the two cents,
he could have--

27:47.583 --> 27:49.000
LINDA: Don't start that again,
okay, Perry?

27:49.083 --> 27:51.000
MASON: I'm-- I'm not.
I'm-- I'm absolutely not.

27:51.083 --> 27:53.834
I'm-- look, I am--
I am so sorry.

27:53.917 --> 27:56.041
LINDA: He just walked in.
You wanna talk to him?

27:56.125 --> 27:58.000
Yes, please.
Thank you, Linda.

