of accusations,

46:57.250 --> 46:58.625
however baseless--

46:58.709 --> 47:00.208
Are we going to lose?

47:00.959 --> 47:02.625
I think...

47:02.709 --> 47:06.166
I know that I can get you
a reduced sentence.

47:06.250 --> 47:08.333
T-- T-- Twenty years, tops,

47:08.417 --> 47:10.709
and as harsh as that may sound--

47:10.792 --> 47:13.625
You want me to say
that I'm guilty?

47:14.333 --> 47:15.417
E.B.: I...

47:20.250 --> 47:22.792
There's a place...

47:22.875 --> 47:25.792
in a town called Chino.

47:25.875 --> 47:27.291
It-- It's for women only.

47:27.375 --> 47:29.583
I'm told
that it's quite acceptable.

47:29.667 --> 47:30.875
(EMILY QUIVERS)

47:32.000 --> 47:33.583
Twenty years?

47:36.000 --> 47:37.583
Mr. Jonathan.

47:40.417 --> 47:42.875
(WEAKLY) When the state, Emily--

47:45.125 --> 47:48.583
The power of the state
wants to crush you,

47:49.500 --> 47:51.583
no matter how minor
your transgression

47:51.667 --> 47:52.917
might seem to be.

47:53.375 --> 47:54.375
It--

47:54.458 --> 47:57.625
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

47:58.333 --> 48:01.417
(SOBS QUIETLY)

48:06.625 --> 48:07.625
No.

48:08.792 --> 48:10.583
No, we won't do this.

48:10.667 --> 48:11.834
Will we?

48:11.917 --> 48:13.500
You're gonna fight.

48:13.583 --> 48:15.959
Because I believe in you, yes?

48:16.041 --> 48:17.208
You're gonna fight.

48:17.291 --> 48:18.875
Let me hear you say it.

48:18.959 --> 48:21.208
I am-- I am going to fight.

48:21.291 --> 48:22.500
E.B.: G-- Good girl.

48:23.792 --> 48:26.500
And you are gonna help me,
aren't you?

48:28.792 --> 48:30.834
I promise. I'll do what's best.

48:31.959 --> 48:35.375
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

48:43.625 --> 48:46.041
Uh, will you open up here,
please?

49:16.834 --> 49:20.375
There is no way you can get
off the phone there

49:20.458 --> 49:23.417
and make it all the way
over here before Emily

49:23.500 --> 49:25.500
is screaming for the cops.

49:25.583 --> 49:26.834
What's the hurry?

49:26.917 --> 49:28.542
Everybody's looking
at the dead kid.

49:28.625 --> 49:30.625
Could have strolled.
Stopped for tea even.

49:30.709 --> 49:32.750
MASON: These guys
are looking at a murder rap.

49:32.834 --> 49:34.166
Had every detail thought out.

49:34.250 --> 49:36.750
They're not risking a long walk
into a hornet's nest.

49:39.083 --> 49:42.542
So maybe our fourth guy,
he's-- he's waiting nearby.

49:43.875 --> 49:46.875
Matthew leaves the money
just sitting here,

49:46.959 --> 49:48.291
the room is empty,

49:48.375 --> 49:50.458
and this guy,
this fourth fucking guy,

49:50.542 --> 49:52.583
just has to reach in,

49:52.667 --> 49:55.458
grab the suitcase and...

49:57.083 --> 49:58.333
Head thatta way.

49:58.417 --> 50:01.542
Out to Hill Street, toward
the screaming mother

50:01.625 --> 50:03.792
and gathering crowds.

50:03.875 --> 50:05.417
That seem likely to you?

50:06.750 --> 50:08.667
PETE:
Not entirely.

50:08.750 --> 50:11.166
Or through this building
out the back.

50:11.250 --> 50:13.709
Vanishing like the blush
of innocence.

50:15.041 --> 50:17.125
What? Something I read.

50:17.208 --> 50:19.834
After you, Mr. Keats.

50:19.917 --> 50:23.500
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

50:23.583 --> 50:26.000
MAINTENANCE MAN:
Used to be pretty much full,

50:26.083 --> 50:29.417
business types, mostly,
before the crash anyways.

50:31.750 --> 50:33.375
And you should know
I was thanking God

50:33.458 --> 50:36.500
this here a short building
on that day.

50:36.583 --> 50:40.250
Ain't wanting to clean up
after no splattered money men.

50:40.333 --> 50:44.291
Did have a hanging though
in 215, used his belt.

50:44.375 --> 50:45.709
This the only way out
the back?

50:45.792 --> 50:47.917
MAINTENANCE MAN: Right through
this door here, yes, sir.

50:50.709 --> 50:52.417
MASON: What the hell is that?

50:53.458 --> 50:54.667
MAINTENANCE MAN: Skyway.

50:54.750 --> 50:57.291
Connects this building
with the Elk's Club there.

50:58.125 --> 51:00.667
I suppose you can get out
that way.

51:02.834 --> 51:04.583
If you had a mind to.

51:10.542 --> 51:13.625
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

51:37.667 --> 51:39.125
How do, friends?

51:40.333 --> 51:42.000
Can't quite place your faces.

51:42.083 --> 51:43.125
Visiting members?

51:43.208 --> 51:45.041
Actually, we was thinking about
joining up.

51:45.125 --> 51:46.625
Might we look around some?

51:46.709 --> 51:49.458
Go ahead.
We're all brothers here.

51:49.542 --> 51:51.291
MASON: Brotherly love.

51:52.000 --> 51:53.917
Fidelity, charity, and justice.

51:54.000 --> 51:55.625
ELK'S CLUB MEMBER:
Our cardinal virtues.

51:55.709 --> 51:58.000
Believe those,
and you're practically an Elk.

51:58.083 --> 52:00.750
The fidelity one,
that a deal breaker?

52:00.834 --> 52:04.834
♪ (BOY SINGING IN DISTANCE) ♪

52:04.917 --> 52:06.583
It's the poor little ones.

52:07.250 --> 52:08.333
Do you mind if we...?

52:08.417 --> 52:10.291
-ELK'S CLUB MEMBER: Please.
-Thank you.

52:10.375 --> 52:13.625
♪ (BOY CONTINUES SINGING) ♪

52:13.709 --> 52:15.291
♪ Where you are ♪

52:15.375 --> 52:18.875
♪ Someone far from harbor
You may guide across the bar ♪

52:18.959 --> 52:22.834
♪ Brighten the corner
Where you are ♪

52:23.875 --> 52:25.166
(APPLAUSE)

52:27.959 --> 52:31.500
EMCEE: Well, isn't that
the real Angel's Flight?

52:31.583 --> 52:33.291
Let's hear it, friends.

52:33.375 --> 52:35.000
(APPLAUSE)

52:35.792 --> 52:39.375
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

52:42.208 --> 52:45.375
EMCEE: I know we all want to do
whatever we can

52:45.458 --> 52:47.500
for these kids.

52:47.583 --> 52:50.458
And nothing's better
for a sickly disposition

52:50.542 --> 52:53.709
-than fresh air and sunshine.
-♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

52:53.792 --> 52:57.417
But before we send them up
to Big Bear for the summer,

52:57.500 --> 53:00.500
we need to raise the cash.

53:00.583 --> 53:01.750
Now...

53:03.458 --> 53:08.333
I have here a dandy set
of gold-plated antlers

53:08.417 --> 53:11.667
that any Elk will be proud of.

53:11.750 --> 53:13.000
What can you bid?

53:13.083 --> 53:14.250
MALE AUCTION ATTENDEE:
Got one here!

53:14.333 --> 53:16.041
-FEMALE AUCTION ATTENDEE: Two!
-Three.

53:16.917 --> 53:19.417
EMCEE: I have three.
Do I hear four?

53:19.500 --> 53:20.917
Can I hear four?

53:21.417 --> 53:22.500
Three-fifty.

53:22.583 --> 53:24.041
EMCEE: Three-fifty.

53:24.125 --> 53:25.375
Do I hear four?

53:25.458 --> 53:27.417
-MALE AUCTION ATTENDEE: Four!
-I didn't know you cared.

53:27.500 --> 53:30.458
-FEMALE AUCTION MEMBER: 4.25.
-My nine-year-old's
on the left with the braids.

53:30.542 --> 53:33.000
-MALE AUCTION ATTENDEE:
Four and a half.
-ENNIS: The hell you doing here?

53:33.083 --> 53:34.792
Just looking for justice.

53:34.875 --> 53:37.083
Charity. Can I count
on you support?

53:37.166 --> 53:38.709
Oh, you don't get my vote.

53:38.792 --> 53:41.208
Not much brotherly love,

53:41.291 --> 53:43.083
but a lot of coincidence.

53:43.166 --> 53:44.166
Oh, how's that?

53:44.250 --> 53:46.500
You, member of this lodge,
one building over

53:46.583 --> 53:48.208
from where the kidnappers
staked out.

53:48.291 --> 53:49.875
I'm here two
or three times a week, pal.

53:49.959 --> 53:51.625
It's my social club.
That's why I'm social.

53:51.709 --> 53:53.166
-Were you here that night?
-I don't know.

53:53.250 --> 53:54.542
Run me in and find out.

53:54.625 --> 53:57.041
Would you hold up
as well as Emily Dodson?

53:57.125 --> 54:00.000
You're like every amateur dick
I ever met.

54:00.083 --> 54:02.709
Think you caught a fish, all
you done is hook your own ass.

54:02.792 --> 54:05.208
Oh, no, I'm too stupid to think
I'm right.

54:05.291 --> 54:07.834
-Nine dollars.
-EMCEE: I have nine.

54:07.917 --> 54:09.375
Do I hear ten?

54:10.208 --> 54:11.417
Ten?

54:11.500 --> 54:13.333
Nine going once.

54:13.750 --> 54:14.917
Twice.

54:15.000 --> 54:16.083
Sold!

54:16.166 --> 54:18.041
Thank you, brother.

54:18.125 --> 54:21.125
(APPLAUSE)

54:23.250 --> 54:25.250
I hope she has a great summer.

54:25.333 --> 54:28.333
EMCEE: Next, we have a silver
loving cup,

54:28.417 --> 54:32.917
beautifully engraved
with a majestic bull elk.

54:33.000 --> 54:36.500
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

55:16.542 --> 55:18.083
(WATER POURING)

55:18.166 --> 55:21.250
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

56:58.709 --> 57:00.291
(STOVE HISSING)

57:19.417 --> 57:22.500
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

57:31.166 --> 57:34.250
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

57:39.709 --> 57:42.750
(INHALES DEEPLY)

57:55.875 --> 57:58.375
(GASPING)

58:11.792 --> 58:14.917
♪ (THEME MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

1:00:12.709 --> 1:00:14.917
We have promising evidence
coming in.

1:00:15.000 --> 1:00:17.542
You're being railroaded, Emily,
and it's wrong.

1:00:17.625 --> 1:00:18.959
But I can help you.

1:00:19.041 --> 1:00:20.333
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

1:00:20.417 --> 1:00:21.667
MAN:
Look, I'm on the Dodson case.

1:00:21.750 --> 1:00:24.166
This guy, Joe Ennis?
Things ain't adding up.

1:00:25.208 --> 1:00:26.875
Let's you and me have a talk.

1:00:27.792 --> 1:00:29.917
The age of miracles
is here again!

1:00:30.000 --> 1:00:30.959
(SOBBING)

1:00:31.041 --> 1:00:32.375
Can I be saved, sister?

1:00:32.542 --> 1:00:34.667
You're here for a reason.
You and me both.

1:00:35.500 --> 1:00:39.083
WOMAN: Stashing evidence,
hidden secrets...

1:00:39.959 --> 1:00:41.417
Just how illegal is this?

1:00:42.041 --> 1:00:43.709
The way I see it,
there's what's legal

1:00:43.792 --> 1:00:45.250
and there's what's right.

1:00:45.750 --> 1:00:47.375
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪
